   V2I technology implemented in third phase of Beaumont’s driverless
   shuttle program

   10 September 2019

V2I technology implemented in third phase of Beaumont’s driverless shuttle
program

   09 September 2019, Beaumont, Canada – ELA, or the Electric Autonomous
   shuttle (using the EasyMile EZ10 autonomous shuttle), has added the
   vehicle-to-infrastructure (V2I) technology in its third phase of the
   pilot program that enables the shuttle to interact wirelessly with
   traffic lights, lane markings and signs. The ELA has been operating
   since May in Beaumont along a one kilometre route.

   ELA is the first time an autonomous vehicle has been fully integrated
   with traffic, pedestrians and traffic infrastructure in western Canada.

   News Sources:
   CTV News Edmonton

   Photo Credit: CTV News Edmonton

